s": 499}, "id": "4a9ee311-eecd-9ba0-9f88-84f750db5fde"}, "input": {"input": ["FINK:Fink found that 5% of 392 internal medicine inpatients had somatization disorder under ICD-10 criteria, while only 1.5% under DSM-IV criteria", "MDE WAAL:Mde Waal reported a prevalence of 16.1% for undifferentiated somatoform disorder", "MULLICK:Mullick found that among 112 children and adolescents with somatoform disorders, girls were diagnosed with somatization disorder and somatoform pain more frequently than boys", "崔利军:崔利军 et al. found the prevalence of somatoform disorders in the general population of Hebei Province to be 0.692%, with somatization disorder at 0.03%, undifferentiated somatoform disorder at 0.24%, pain disorder at 0.56%, and hypochondriasis at 0.18%", "孟凡强:孟凡强 et al. found that 18.2% of outpatients in general hospitals had somatoform disorders, with somatization disorder accounting for 7.4% of total outpatient visits", "HEBEI PROVINCE:Hebei Province is the location where 崔利军 et al. conducted their survey on the prevalence of somatoform disorders", "综合医院:综合医院（General Hospital）是一种提供多种医疗服务的大型医疗机构，涵盖广泛的医疗领域，包括精神卫生服务。在中国，综合医院积极建立或已经设立了精神科或提供精神卫生服务的专业部门，以应对患者的精神健康问题。这些医院特别注重实施会诊-联络精神病学（Consultation-Liaison Psychiatry, CLP）服务，旨在为患有身体疾病的患者提供全面的精神健康支持。CLP服务涉及处理各种精神健康问题，包括器质性精神障碍和心身疾病。此外，综合医院也是研究的重要场所，例如孟凡强等学者曾在综合医院的门诊患者中进行了关于躯体形式障碍的研究。总体而言，综合医院在提供综合性医疗服务的同时，也在精神卫生领域发挥着重要作用，致力于改善患者的身心健康。", "DSM-III-R:", "BRIQUET SYNDROME:Briquet Syndrome is a term used to describe somatic symptom disorder characterized by multiple, recurring physical symptoms without a clear medical cause", "HYPOCONDRIASIS:Hypochondriasis is a mental health condition where individuals are excessively worried about having a serious illness despite medical reassurance"], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}